  "prompt": "Is a passport compulsory to travel on flights within India?",
  "response": "In India, a valid government-issued photo ID is compulsory for domestic air travel, but it does not necessarily have to be a passport. Acceptable forms of identification include:\n\n1. Passport\n2. Voter ID card\n3. Driving license\n4. Aadhaar card\n5. PAN card\n6. Government-issued photo ID cards\n\nWhile a passport is not mandatory for domestic flights within India, passengers are advised to carry a valid photo ID for security and identification purposes.",
